  , issueCommentBody =
      "In my case, I let people write something like that\r\n```\r\nPost = thinky.createModel(\"post\");\r\nAuthor = thinky.createModel(\"author\");\r\n\r\nPost.hasOne(Author, \"author\");\r\n\r\nPost.get(\"idValue\").run().then(function(result) {\r\n    // returns null if \"idValue\" is not found\r\n    // returns a document from the table \"post\"\r\n})\r\n\r\nPost.get(\"idValue\").getJoin().run().then(function(result) {\r\n    // returns a post with the field \"author\" corresponding to the related author\r\n}).error(function(error) {\r\n    // returns an error if idValue is not found\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf possible, I would like the same behavior with or without `getJoin`.\r\n\r\n\r\nHaving `null.merge({foo:\"bar\"})` always return `null` seems a little weird to me. In my case,\r\n`default` doesn't work too."
